"7:109:9" : {s: 7, a: 109, w: 9, r: "علم", t: "عَلِيمٌۭ", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "ʿalīmun", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী",e: "learned", b: "মহাজ্ঞানী", i: "yang pandai", f: 100, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows.", ag: "صفة نكرة", eg: "Adjective Indefinite state", tag: "ADJ", pos: "ADJ", att: "INDEF", qual: "NOM", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَعْلَمُ،عَلِمَ،عَلِيمٌۢ"},
"7:110:1" : {s: 7, a: 110, w: 1, r: "رود", t: "يُرِيدُ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "yurīdu", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "He wants", b: "চান", i: "dia bermaksud", f: 38, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.).", ag: "فعل مضارع صيغة ٤", eg: "Verb Imperfect 4th form", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPF", qual: "(IV)", deg: "3", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَرَادَ"},
